About the OCC Charter

BankNet is the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency's (OCC) site for communicating with and receiving information from national banks and federal savings associations. BankNet is only available to OCC-regulated banks and is not available to the public. Click here for more information.

Alerts and Outages

  • Alert: BankNet will be unavailable from 6:00 AM EDT Saturday, April 20, 2019 through 2:00 PM EDT Sunday, April 21, 2019. We apologize for any inconvenience.
  • BankNet works best with newer Internet browsers. Use Internet Explorer 9 or later, Firefox, or Chrome to have the best experience with the site.

For technical assistance, contact the BankNet Help Desk by phone or e-mail.

Monday to Friday, 7:00 a.m. to 11:00 p.m. ET

Phone: 800-641-5925
E-mail: BankNet@occ.treas.gov

Please Note: You are entering an official U.S. government computer network. In entering this system, you acknowledge your responsibility under applicable laws and policies and agree to maintain the security and privacy of all information contained herein. You agree that you will use this system for authorized purposes only. Your behavior on the system may be monitored, recorded, and subject to audit. Use of the information system indicates consent to monitoring and recording. Unauthorized, inappropriate, or illegal uses are punishable by criminal prosecution or administrative sanction.
